<br>
     These new &quot;national&quot; competitions may be the driving, changing force. If they catch on, they will be. The people who'll win them and come close will be younger. Some much younger. They will start becoming the &quot;celebrities&quot; in the sport, alongside, I think, the older known guys. They won't &quot;push them aside&quot;, fly fishing's too traditional for this to happen. Anyway, it's one reason why good fishin young guys are getting into these things. It's virtually the only way they can become noticed, aside from if they are incredibly innovative, talented,  and truely head and shoulders in ability above everybody else as a fisherman. An example of this from yesteryear might be Stu Apte. There are few Stu Aptes in the history of the world. So you win competitions instead.<br>
<br>
       You'll also notice how few &quot;big names&quot; will take part in these things too. They know already that the very talented younger guys are going to win these things, and anyway it's just too big a risk for them (as they see it). See, they know they've had a pretty good thing going on, noteriety wise, for all these years. But no longer. No longer, that is, if the events catch on. This &quot;younger&quot; guy you mention, John, probably feels the same as the &quot;older&quot; ones, by the way. What they all may not realize is that they will still be no less noticed. It's just that the younger guys will be noticed as well. This is a wonderful and healthy change for fly fishing.  For note: the older &quot;celebs&quot; who do enter the competitions are to be given much credit, win or &quot;lose&quot;, they ARE special.<br>
        Think about it. Bass competitions already did this to bass fishing. Made the young guys &quot;stars&quot;. Before them it was the old &quot;geezers&quot; who knew &quot;how to get em&quot;.<br>
<br>
    So John and Andrew, or anybody, if you really are legitimately that good, it's simply just a matter of time. I don't mean thirtey years either. I mean a relatively short span. Looks like you were born at the right time.  Hey wait! Whose to say, actually. If you were here thirtey years before you were, maybe you'd be there already!<br>
<br>
     Best of luck this weekend guys!<br>
<br>
                                              All My Best,<br>
